LENORE.

. When Poe was a student of the Academy at Richmond, Va„ a boy at this time about . Sixteen years old, he was invited by a friend to visit his home. Poe found there au unusually attractive and happy household. The mother was a beautiful woman, with tender heart aud affectlonate disposition. She felt great sympathy and compassion for Poe on account of his orphanage. Poe was deeply touched by the kindness of his friend's mother who died soon afterward. He never forgot her gentle spirit. and this, in imagination‚ he embodied in a younger person *of peculiar charms, and celebrated it in the poem of “ Lenore.’' This is one of his finest productions and shows the better side of his character.
